File: Pretoria was flooded with traffic on Tuesday morning. TSHWANE - Power has been restored in Pretoria following a massive power outage on Tuesday. Earlier, the city was flooded with heavy traffic after parts of Pretoria were without electricity due to a 132kV trip at the Njala substation. READ: Traffic jam in Tshwane following power outage Technicians were deployed to investigate the untimely black-out and have since managed to remedy the situation. Executive Mayor, Stevens Mokgalapa was on-site at 12:00 to check on the progress made and he assured residents that all power would be back on by 14:00. The city is appealing to residents who are still without power to report it so that technicians can be dispatched.